<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- C major allows entirely natural voicings — no accidentals in harp parts
- Bars 0-4 (phrase A): Dm-F-C-G-Am pattern; 2-note RH opening, 4-note LH
- Bars 5-8 (repeat A): varied inversions — Dm 2nd inv, C 1st inv, Dm7
- Bars 9-11 (bridge): G sustained creates tension; G→Em voice leading
- Bars 12-15 (coda): Am-Em-F-Dm descending chain, Dm final

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 11: G→Em — B3 and G3 held as common tones, E descends E2→E2 (held)
- Bar 13: Am→F progression — C4 drops to A3, smooth inner voice
- Bars 14-15: Dm→Am→Dm — submediant substitution creates ii-vi-ii plagal feel

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 0-4: light 2-note RH, introduction builds gradually
- Bars 5-8: richer inversions, 3-note RH appears
- Bars 9-12: climax region, full 3+4 voicing on most beats
- Bars 13-15: final descent, concluding Dm root position whole note
-->
